One of the hosts of Euro 2020, Italy, have qualified for the knockout stage, following their 3-0 win over Switzerland on Wednesday night. Roberto Manciniâ€™s men came into the game top of Group A, after they beat Turkey 3-0 in their first game. Manuel Locatelli bagged a brace against the Swiss, while Ciro Immobile grabbed a late goal. This takes the Italians up to six points and into the next round. They will be joined from Group A by either Switzerland or Wales. The Welsh beat Turkey 2-0 earlier in the day, to eliminate them from the competition.